headline: Archer-Daniels-Midland (NYSE:ADM) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q3 CY2025 Earnings
summary: Agricultural supply chain giant Archer-Daniels-Midland (NYSE:ADM) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025 as sales rose 2.2% year on year to $20.37 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.92 per share was 7.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Archer-Daniels-Midland: Too Much Policy Risk For A Low-Margin Dividend King
summary: Archer-Daniels-Midland stock held amid weak guidance, policy risks, and fair valuation. Learn why analysts remain cautious on ADM despite strong financials.
